    "body": "Some config files, (especially packages.yaml, to describe system packages) really need to be different per-operating-system, as opposed to just per-platform, if you have a shared packages area.  This lets you have an etc/spack/scientific7/packages.yaml and an etc/spack/debian6/packages.yaml, and so on  to describe system packages available  on assorted operating systems.\r\n\r\nResolves #4427",
